  "texts": [
    "Finally, they use multi-label classifiers to determine the entity class.",
    "The authors compare their approach to 8 state-of-the-art methods (FIGMENT [190], CUTE [186], MuLR [191], Global [128], Corpus [189], PTE [175], Planetoid [196] and ASNE [104]).In their second work, Jin et al. [87] convert entities in the KB into three semantic graphs.",
    "Each graph represents a specific kind of correlation among entities.",
    "The first one (Aco) is dedicated to representing the co-occurrence relations among entities.",
    "The second one (Acat) represents the category-proximity between entities."
  ],
